{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/how-to-create-an-animated-choropleth-map-with-less-than-15-lines-of-code-2ff04921c60b", "time": 1683009898.259074, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/how-to-create-an-animated-choropleth-map-with-less-than-15-lines-of-code-2ff04921c60b/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "How to Create an Animated Choropleth Map with Less Than 15 Lines of Code | Towards Data Science", "h1": "How to Create an Animated Choropleth Map with Less Than 15 Lines of Code", "description": "In this article, you will learn how easy to create animated choropleth maps using Plotly and Python on Jupyter."}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://plotly.com/python/animations/", "anchor_text": "Plotly Express", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://plotly.com/python/getting-started/", "anchor_text": "Plotly installed", "paragraph_index": 2}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Choropleth_map", "anchor_text": "choropleth map", "paragraph_index": 3}, {"url": "https://plotly.com/python/choropleth-maps/", "anchor_text": "Plotly Express", "paragraph_index": 3}, {"url": "https://plotly.com/python/choropleth-maps/", "anchor_text": "the official website", "paragraph_index": 3}, {"url": "https://www.ucrdatatool.gov/Search/Crime/State/StatebyState.cfm", "anchor_text": "published by the FBI", "paragraph_index": 4}, {"url": "https://amaral.northwestern.edu/blog/step-step-how-plot-map-slider-represent-time-evolu", "anchor_text": "Julia Poncela-Casasnovas", "paragraph_index": 4}, {"url": "https://gist.githubusercontent.com/shinokada/f01139d3a024de375ede23cec5d52360/raw/424ac0055ed71a04e6f45badfaef73df96ad0aad/CrimeStatebyState_1960-2014.csv", "anchor_text": "here", "paragraph_index": 4}, {"url": "https://plotly.github.io/plotly.py-docs/generated/plotly.graph_objects.Choropleth.html#plotly-graph-objs-choropleth", "anchor_text": "plotly.graph_objects.choropleth", "paragraph_index": 7}, {"url": "https://plotly.com/python/map-configuration/#named-map-scopes-and-country-subunits", "anchor_text": "scope", "paragraph_index": 7}, {"url": "https://plotly.github.io/datasets/", "anchor_text": "sample datasets", "paragraph_index": 8}, {"url": "https://github.com/plotly/datasets/blob/master/gapminderDataFiveYear.csv", "anchor_text": "Gapminder", "paragraph_index": 8}, {"url": "https://blog.codewithshin.com/membership", "anchor_text": "becoming a member", "paragraph_index": 11}], "all_paragraphs": ["Plotly Express makes it easy to create animated graphs. The official document says that \u201cAlthough Plotly Express supports animation for many chart and map types, smooth inter-frame transitions are today only possible for scatter and bar.\u201d", "Even though choropleth maps are not mentioned, in this article you will find just how easy it is to create animated choropleth maps using Plotly and Python on Jupyter.", "This article assumes you are already familiar with the basic operation in JupyterLab/Jupyter Notebook and you have Plotly installed.", "A choropleth map is a map composed of colored polygons. Plotly Express\u2019 px.choropleth function and the lower-level go.Choropleth graph object can create choropleth maps and you can find some examples on the official website. You can only zoom in or out of the maps.", "We\u2019re going to use the murder rate in the US. Data was originally published by the FBI, and Julia Poncela-Casasnovas modified it. You can find it here.", "The DataFrame\u2019s columns have the following values.", "Import plotly.express and pandas. We create a DataFrame using pd.read_csv. We remove the District of Columbia rows under the State column.", "We instantiate the plotly.graph_objects.choropleth object and set parameters. - location: This parameter sets the coordinates via location IDs or names. We use State_code column values for locations.- color: We use theMurder_per100000 value to change the color of the state.- animation_frame: This allows us to animate and add the play and stop button under the map.- locationmode: determines to match entries in locations to regions on the map. Values are \u201cISO-3\u201d or \u201cUSA-states\u201d. - scope: limits the map to this value. The available scopes are: : 'world', 'usa', 'europe', 'asia', 'africa', 'north america', 'south america'.- rang_color: determines the value of the scale on the right. Use 0 and the max value.- title: is the tile of the map. - height: is the height created map.- color_continuous_scale: We can set any color scheme from the following list.", "Let\u2019s create an animated choropleth world map. Plotly has sample datasets and we\u2019re going to use the Gapminder.", "The official website does not have an example of an animated choropleth map, but it is easy to create using animation_frame and setting proper parameters.", "Are you inspired to try it for your next project?", "Get full access to every story on Medium by becoming a member.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "A programmer and technology enthusiast with a passion for sharing my knowledge and experience."], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2F2ff04921c60b&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fhow-to-create-an-animated-choropleth-map-with-less-than-15-lines-of-code-2ff04921c60b&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fhow-to-create-an-animated-choropleth-map-with-less-than-15-lines-of-code-2ff04921c60b&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://mediu